<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-1301] NPE in FactoryFinder.findClass when context classloader is null</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-1301</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;My program works fine, when I run it as a normal Windows app.  But when I try to run it as a service, it throws a &quot;Could not auto create component: http&quot; which is caused by a NullPointerException which is caused by Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader() returning null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A quick search found this ActiveMQ bug: &lt;a href=&quot;http://issues.apache.org/activemq/browse/AMQ-1229&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://issues.apache.org/activemq/browse/AMQ-1229&lt;/a&gt; which is essentially identical.  If it&apos;s been fixed in ActiveMQ, probably you can just merge the fix from org.apache.activemq.util.FactoryFinder into org.apache.camel.util.FactoryFinder.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Incidentally, the fact that the context classloader is null has also been reported as a bug: &lt;a href=&quot;http://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-100&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-100&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;JRE 1.6.0_11, Commons Daemon 1.0.1, MS Windows XP&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
